    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1864-01-29T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1864-01-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="350"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d350">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                        Pike</persName>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 139.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State,</hi>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1864-01-29">
                            <hi rend="italic">January</hi> 29, 1864.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Your despatch of the 6th of January, No. 118, has
                    been received. The President is especially gratified by the sentiments of
                    kindness and good will towards the United States which were expressed to you by
                    his Majesty on the occasion you have mentioned.</p>
                <p>It is remarkable that the European powers are exercised with debates and even
                    seeking conferences upon the questions how to preserve peace and reduce <pb
                        facs="0329" n="309" xml:id="pg_309"/> armaments in Europe, and yet they at
                    the same time pursue a system that aggravates and prolongs war in America, and
                    forces upon the United States a policy of military preparation incongruous with
                    their history and uncongenial with their natural disposition.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">James S. Pike,</hi> Esq., <hi rend="italic">&amp;c.,
                            &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
